summary: But this one is different though, Carol in the film actually was around to help Maria raise Monica.  Tony meets Peter after Ben...
question: But this one is different though, Carol in the film actually was around to help Maria raise Monica.  Tony meets Peter after Ben and May did all the work.
answer: The point is they’re both unnecessary MCU additions that do nothing but weaken other stand alone (Peter and Monica) characters narratively in the eyes of new fans, which also creates a further divide between comic fans and stubborn movie fans. Tony had no business usurping Ben’s role in Homecoming just like Carol had no business being a replacement for Frank in terms of inspiring Monica in CM.
